@startuml business-process-receive-stock
title Business Process: Receive Stock (Incoming Inventory)

!include skinparams.puml

|Staff/Admin|
start
:Access Receive Stock Page;

|System|
:Display Receive Form;

|Staff/Admin|
:Submit Receive Stock Form;
note right
  The user provides:
  • Supplier and warehouse/zone info
  • Product line items, including SKU,
    quantity, cost, and optional batch
    or serial number details.
end note

|System|
:Validate and Process Stock;
note right
  The system performs a series of actions:
  • Validates all submitted data
  • Creates a receipt record and line items
  • Updates inventory levels, batches, and serials
  • Logs the transaction
  • Updates analytics data
end note

if (Processing Successful?) then (yes)
  :Display Success and Options;
  note right
    A success message with the new receipt
    number is displayed.
    
    Options are provided to:
    • Print the receipt
    • Generate and print labels
  end note
  stop
else (no)
  :Display Validation Errors;
  note right
    If validation fails, specific errors
    are shown, allowing the user to
    correct the form and resubmit.
  end note
  stop
endif

@enduml
